article.headline: Jacksonville 24, Butler 16
article.story: INDIANAPOLIS -- Josh McGregor threw two touchdowns and Jacksonville beat Butler 24-16 Saturday. The Dolphins (9-1, 7-0 Pioneer League) finished with 341 total offense yards to Butler's (4-6, 2-5) 383 yards. McGregor connected with Chris Kuck in the second quarter, and threw a 27-yard TD pass to Josh Philpart in the fourth quarter. Rudell Small also ran for a touchdown, and Josh Hostetler kicked a field goal. McGregor finished 23 of 35 with 263 passing yards. Butler's only TD came from an Andrew Huck pass to Carter Walley with 5:06 left in the first quarter. David Lang also kicked three field goals for the Bulldogs. Huck finished with 248 passing yards. Saturday's game was the eighth win in a row for Jacksonville, the highest scoring team in the conference.
